<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DIAMONDLIFE&#8482; (BOSCH PIN SLIDE) DISC BRAKES For Vehicles Built After June 2, 2002 - OPERATION - ANCHOR
        PLATE AND SPLASH SHIELD
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="operate" graphiccount="2">
        <title>ANCHOR PLATE AND SPLASH SHIELD</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0404708">Figure 8</hotlnk>
            <xref refid="f0404708"/>
            for Items in parentheses.
        </para>
        <para>The caliper (Item 1) is positioned on the anchor plate (Item 2) and mounted to the leading and trailing
            floating guide pins (Items 3 and 4) located at each end of the anchor plate. Caliper hex mounting bolts
            (Item 5) attach the caliper to each guide pin. A tie bar (Item 6) is used for added support on 73 mm pin
            slide disc brakes only.
        </para>
        <figure id="f0404708" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg04/G0404008.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px"/>
            <caption>Figure 8. Anchor Plate and Splash Shield</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>DRIVER SIDE FRONT (73 mm SHOWN)</callout1>
                <callout1>1. CALIPER</callout1>
                <callout1>2. ANCHOR PLATE</callout1>
                <callout1>3. LEADING GUIDE PIN (FLOATING)</callout1>
                <callout1>4. TRAILING GUIDE PIN (FLOATING)</callout1>
                <callout1>5. HEX BOLT (CALIPER MOUNTING)</callout1>
                <callout1>6. TIE BAR</callout1>
                <callout1>7. ROTOR</callout1>
                <callout1>8. SPLASH SHIELD</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0404709">Figure 9</hotlnk>
            <xref refid="f0404709"/>
            for Items in parentheses unless otherwise noted.
        </para>
        <para>The rotors
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0404708">(Item 7, Figure 8)</hotlnk>
            <xref refid="f0404708"/>
            on both front and rear brake groups are protected on the inboard side by a splash shield
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0404708">(Item 8, Figure 8)</hotlnk>
            <xref refid="f0404708"/>. The splash shield (Item 1) is attached to the anchor plate (Item 2) with three
            12-point head bolts (Item 3). Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0404709">Figure 9</hotlnk>
            <xref refid="f0404709"/>
            for proper splash shield mounting on anchor plate for 66 mm and 73 mm brakes.
        </para>
        <figure id="f0404709" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg04/G0404709.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                     scalefitheight="532px"/>
            <caption>Figure 9. Splash Shield Mounting to Anchor Plate</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. SPLASH SHIELD</callout1>
                <callout1>2. ANCHOR PLATE</callout1>
                <callout1>3. 12-POINT HEAD BOLT</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
